name: MCXCJ0317.9-4414
Name: A3112
Comments: Horologium Supercluster with A3128, A3158, A3266. Xray mass is very close to the lensing mass (SZ mass is a bit smaller but within 2-sigma). But it seems there’s an offset between the lensing peak and BCG/X-ray peak. XMM: https://iopscience.iop.org/article/10.1088/0004-637X/747/1/32 (to determine the offset). The depth looks okay (only g band is 0.2 mag shallower than the goal). Very strong correlation between BCG orientation, mass map, RS galaxy distribution! Need to test photoz after adjusting the Y band offset (<0.02mag).
